  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version  of  ppa:ethereum/ethereum-dev : \n\n```\nVersion : 1.5.0-unstable\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6.1\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.6\n```\n\nGeth version  of  ppa:ethereum/ethereum : \n\n```\nVersion : 1.3.6\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6.1\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.6\n```\n\nOS & Version: Xubuntu Xenial Xerus\nCommit hash : (if `develop`) \n#### Expected behaviour\n\ngeth init /path/to/genesis.json  should initialize and exit\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nIt connects to the public block chain and begins synchronization\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nIt works as expected, if I install Ethereum with : \n\n```\n sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:ethereum/ethereum-dev;\n sudo apt-get update;\n sudo apt-get install -y ethereum;\n```\n\nIt misbehaves, if I install Ethereum with : \n\n```\n sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:ethereum/ethereum;\n sudo apt-get update;\n sudo apt-get install -y ethereum;\n```\n\nThe file `/etc/apt/sources.list.d/ethereum-ubuntu-ethereum-dev-xenial.list` contains ...\n\n```\n deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/ethereum/ethereum-dev/ubuntu xenial main\n```\n",
